commentBody:
I appreciated being able to fill in most starred clues without the revealer but, once I got it, it helping with the last two.

Sad there wasn't a single Dumas references in the grid :(

@wordplay: ATLAS also works as the titan from Greek mythology holding the whole sky/world on his shoulders. Clever clue to work both ways.

@Aaron 

Benjamin Franklin once said, “… in this world, nothing can be said to be certain, except death and taxes—unless you’re incorporating in Delaware, in which case only the first thing.”

